The President of Russia, Vladimir Putin, has signed a law to impose administrative liability for the violation of the time limit and the procedure for the payment of goods (work, services) in the procurement of public and municipal needs.
The Act is intended to address the very serious problem of non-fulfilment of obligations by customers in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation in which businessmen were not able to receive payment under existing State and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia commissioned the Office of the Attorney-General of the Russian Federation to take the problem for special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not deal with unscrupulous bidders who entered into unfinished contracts, made every effort to evade their payment obligations, and included illegal terms in the contracts.
The problem was system-wide in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of businessmen to be paid by public order, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office has made 9,000 submissions, with 4,500 officials being subject to disciplinary action, 533 administrative officers, and 75 files have been submitted to the investigating bodies for the organization of the procedural review, 46 of which have been subject to criminal proceedings.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles of business debt was paid.
These massive sums, however, have not been accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for much more modest sums have led to immense debts.
Here's the case.
The manager of a small company won a competition for social transport services for a few million roubles.
The man invested all his working capital, fully met his obligations, but he didn't get the money on time.
The result is an increasing financial coma of wage, tax, credit that would have led to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur had not sought the help of the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been overcome as far as possible in a number of regions.
However, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt on State and municipal contracts identified by the procurators of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical levels, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office is working in a manual crisis management regime.
The Attorney-General personally holds field meetings with the local authorities to deal in a substantive manner with all the violations that have been detected by the prosecutors and to address them without delay.
Such operational meetings have already been held in Jaroslavla and Yekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ “On the amendment of the Code of Administrative Offences with regard to the administrative liability of the employer's officials for the violation of the time and procedure for the payment of goods (work, services) in the procurement of public and municipal needs”, which was signed last week by the President of the Russian Federation.
The draft law was drawn up by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Office of the Attorney-General.
The new Act will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences with an article which provides for a fine of between 30,000 and 50,000 roubles for breaching the time limit and the procedure for the payment of goods, work and services by an official of the employer in State and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been administratively punished for a similar offence, he or she will be disqualified for a period of from one to two years.
All the procurators of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to implement these legislative innovations in practice.
The Civil Rights Unit has issued a travel warning to Missouri.
The National Association for the Advancement of Colored Populations has issued a warning to colored people travelling to Missouri due to the discriminatory state policy and racist attacks.
The group's statement is as follows: “Warning for travelers of the National Association for the Advancement of the Colored Population, valid until August 28, 2017, calls on African American travelers, visitors and Missouri citizens to be particularly careful and cautious in their travels through the state in connection with a number of dubious racist incidents that have recently taken place all over the state and are here”.
