Previously, the American Union for the Defence of Civil Liberties (ACLU) had issued warnings to travelers in Texas and Arizona after these states had enacted new immigration control laws, under which local law enforcement agencies had been ordered to arrest people for violating immigration laws, which ACLU believed should have increased the number of checks based on race.
