Gobai says that the Paniai, like the other popuas, view their voice for Jokowi as a debt to be paid.
"They don't need money, they just want justice," he says.
Despite threats and intimidation, the families of the victims of the Paniai shooting carried out the last symbolic act of insubordination, burying the body of one of the victims on a plot of land in front of the police and the military station.
Knowing that justice may never be done, at least they will not let the guilty forget their crimes.
“A member of our family was killed,” says Jacobus without raising his head.
"What else were we supposed to do?"
