We were told, "You must be very brave people who came to us today."
But our task is to show that we do not support just Haftar, we are engaged in a dialogue with all the key players in the conflict in Libya.
You and Haftar have been in touch.
Does it make it easier to have an understanding with Russian partners on a human, emotional level that he has been studying twice in the USSR?
And, by the way, does Haftar know Russian?
Russian, if he knows, it's very relative.
