But Islamists are part of his coalition.
Yes, but it is his own position that Libya must be a completely normal country - a moderately Islamic, open world.
And he is also active in the fight against terrorists.
How does he have such a reputation?
It is created by those countries that do not want Russia to be in contact with Tripoli.
Tripoli is the capital, and there is a legislative, executive, and judicial power.
There's a national oil corporation, a national bank, and other State entities.
Of course, some countries wanted us to stay out of it.
And we mixed up all the charts and began to be active with both Tripoli and Tobrook.
We are already reaping the benefits of this work: Rosneft has entered into a cooperation agreement with the Libyan State Oil Company, NOC.
